5|$|Communications usually {{consisted}} of FuG X, the later FuG 10 (Funkgerät), navigational <b>direction</b> <b>finder</b> PeilG V <b>direction</b> <b>finder</b> (PeilG - Peilgerät) and the FuG 25 IFF and FuBI 1 blind-landing devices. The crew communicated by EiV intercom. A primitive autopilot device, the Siemens K4Ü, was installed and could maintain bearing using the rudder's control surfaces.|$|E
